p"><p>Here is a recording of my recent livestream.</p><p>Topics covered:</p=
><ul><li><p><span>My </span><a href=3D"https://www.robkhenderson.com/p/a-se=
x-strike-isnt-going-to-work" rel=3D"">recent essay</a><span> on sex strikes=
 and the =E2=80=9C4B=E2=80=9D movement</span></p></li><li><p>Discussion of =
some strategy and game theory from the superb book =E2=80=9CThe Strategy of=
 Conflict=E2=80=9D by Thomas Schelling </p></li><li><p>Differences between =
threats and promises in strategy and negotiation</p></li><li><p>Establishin=
g credibility through strategic failure</p></li><li><p>In an abduction scen=
ario, what game theory says you should do to convince your captor that you =
won=E2=80=99t go to the police if he releases you</p></li><li><p>The strate=
gic use of perceived instability or irrationality to achieve your objective=
s</p></li><li><p>Similarities between the 4B Movement and MGTOW (men going =
their own way)</p></li><li><p>The cultural shift stigmatizing tobacco while=
 normalizing marijuana</p></li><li><p>Book recommendations</p></li><li><p><=
span>Anti-natalism (believing it=E2=80=99s wrong to have children) </span><=
a href=3D"https://x.com/robkhenderson/status/1541518558932377601" rel=3D"">=
correlates</a><span> with the </span><a href=3D"https://www.robkhenderson.c=
om/p/understanding-the-dark-triad-personality" rel=3D"">Dark Triad personal=
ity traits</a><span> (narcissism, psychopathy, and Machiavellianism). I sug=
gest the possibility that anti-natalism is an a unconscious reproductive in=
terference strategy (although modern dynamics complicate this hypothesis)</=
span></p></li><li><p>Answering questions from livestream viewers</p></li></=
ul><p>A few thoughts that occurred during the Q&amp;A portion of this lives=
tream:</p><p>4B frames itself as politically motivated. Still, 45% of women=
 who participated in the recent election voted for Trump, and roughly 45% o=
f men voted for Harris. If the goal is to punish Trump voters, you'd expect=
 4B to be a gender-neutral movement aimed at withholding sex and romance fr=
om all Trump supporters.</p><p>Instead, it's a group of women focused on pu=
nishing men specifically. This makes it seem less like a political statemen=
t and more like a way to inflict punishment on men under the guise of radic=
al political action.</p><p>There are similarities between the 4B movement a=
nd the MGTOW movement. MGTOW, or "Men Going Their Own Way," believe women a=
ren't worth the emotional, financial, or personal investment and advocate f=
or men to "go their own way," avoiding relationships with women entirely.</=
p><p>The 4B movement seems to be a mirror image of that. Though MGTOW, as I=
 understand it, is meant to be permanent. It promotes a monastic lifestyle =
where men disengage entirely from women, and the act of withdrawal itself i=
s the end goal. The 4B movement, on the other hand, has a specific politica=
l aim. It encourages withholding sex as a means to achieve that political e=
nd. While both movements are rooted in frustration with the opposite sex, M=
GTOW's withdrawal is the goal, while 4B uses withdrawal as a tactic.</p><p>=
I suspect many women in this movement may not like men much in general. Sim=
ilar to how men in MGTOW say it's about independence or whatever but really=
 they just don't like women. The political framing might just be a convenie=
nt way to express these sentiments publicly without looking romantically bi=
tter.</p><div><hr></div><p>All subscribers (both free and paid) were able t=
o watch it live, but only paid subscribers have access to the full recordin=
